KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala spoke with eNCA's Faith Mangope. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC stalwart Meshack Radebe has passed away after a short illness.
Radebe played a key role in securing peace between warring factions of the ANC and IFP in Hammarsdale in KwaZulu-Natal in the late 1980s and 90s. He served as a Member of the Provincial Legislature and was MEC for Social development and also Agriculture and Environmental Affairs. KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala has hailed Radebe as one of the greatest sons of the province. IFP President Emeritus Mangosuthu Buthelezi has paid his respects calling Radebe a friend of peace and champion of reconciliation.